668
01:04:29,420 --> 01:04:33,957
Because the point is to find exactly what is wrong in his reasoning.

669
01:04:34,320 --> 01:04:36,635
His reasoning is very simple, basically.

670
01:04:37,601 --> 01:04:39,078
He starts with this problem.

671
01:04:39,360 --> 01:04:52,876
Why is it that most of us find it more problematic, much more problematic, to torture somebody in front of us than to push a button which will kill hundreds of thousand people out there, out of our sight?

672
01:04:53,400 --> 01:05:00,038
He claims he calls this the moon illusion, in parallel with this old perceptual illusion.

673
01:05:00,521 --> 01:05:05,440
If you don't know how it is, you think the moon is just a small object out there in the sky.

674
01:05:05,480 --> 01:05:12,374
But he said, in the same way that we know now rationally that moon is a quite large object,

675
01:05:13,480 --> 01:05:18,556
that we should do the same restructuring of our ethical experience.

676
01:05:19,020 --> 01:05:21,217
So for him, it's a pretty horrifying conclusion.

677
01:05:21,580 --> 01:05:24,618
The fact that we cannot torture, most of us at least,

678
