somebody face to face is simply, I quote him,

679
01:05:28,940 --> 01:05:37,576
the reason for this inability to torture another person is every bit as neurological as those that give rise to the moon illusion.

680
01:05:37,920 --> 01:05:39,672
So simply, let's grow up.

681
01:05:41,040 --> 01:05:44,177
Let's learn to put things in proper proportion.

682
01:05:44,660 --> 01:05:48,998
And following a ruthless utilitarian calculation,

683
01:05:49,560 --> 01:05:58,558
let's become aware that it's even your duty, as he puts it, to torture somebody in front of you if in this way you can prevent much larger suffering.

684
01:05:58,940 --> 01:06:05,237
Now, Harris concedes that, nonetheless, we cannot simply outgrow our deeply ingrained habits.

685
01:06:05,621 --> 01:06:09,993
So he proposed something which I think is even more tasteless, a kind of a truth pill.

686
01:06:11,441 --> 01:06:18,594
